-- Hungary’s State Mobile Firm to Call Network Tender, Nemzet Says
-- B y   E d i t h   B a l a z s
-- 2012-06-14T06:19:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-14/hungary-s-state-mobile-firm-to-call-network-tender-nemzet-says.html
Hungary’s state-owned mobile service
provider may call a tender for network expansion within weeks,
 Magyar Nemzet  reported, citing unidentified people.  China ’s Huawei Technologies Co. and  ZTE Corp. (000063) ,  Ericsson (ERICB)  AB
and Nokia Siemens Networks are interested in bidding, according
to the Budapest-based newspaper.  Hungary’s fourth mobile service provider will start
operations in early 2013, Nemzet said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
 ebalazs1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  